    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 5 Engine Service Manual - Crankcase, Crankshaft, and Camshaft -
        Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="s26508.3">
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcproc id="s26508.3.1" svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="2">
            <title>Camshaft Bushings</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, use the correct Camshaft Bushing Remover / Installer (expanding
                        collet). See
                        <hotlnk document="eges390_351.xml" xrefid="E30009C">Special Service Tools
                            <xref refid="E30009C"/>
                        </hotlnk>
                        .
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f3000938" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd06/D0629.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Camshaft bushing installation</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Oil supply hole</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Pulling screw</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Backup nut</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft Bushing Remover/Installer (expanding collet)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft bushing</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft bushing oil supply slot</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, and to ensure proper oil circulation through the crankcase, make
                        sure all camshaft bushing oil slots are aligned with corresponding oil supply holes machined in
                        the crankcase.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide a new bushing onto the Camshaft Bushing Remover / Installer (expanding collet).
                    See
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_351.xml" xrefid="E30009C">Special Service Tools
                        <xref refid="E30009C"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Thread pulling screw, backup nut, and Camshaft Bushing Remover / Installer together.
                    Tighten expanding collet by turning backup nut until bushing is held securely on the Camshaft
                    Bushing Remover/Installer.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To aid alignment of bushing and crankcase oil holes, use a marker to indicate oil hole
                    location on backup nut of installation tool. Repeat for each camshaft bushing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install camshaft bushings through rear of crankcase. Pull bushings in place at rear of
                    crankcase by turning pulling nut on pulling screw. Remove Camshaft Bushing Remover/Installer and
                    inspect oil hole alignment.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3000939" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ03/J03030.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Camshaft bushings measurement</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using a
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_351.xml" xrefid="E30009C">telescoping gauge
                        <xref refid="E30009C"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    , measure camshaft bushing inside diameter with bushings installed in crankcase.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Measure telescoping gauge with a 2-3 inch micrometer and record measurement.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To determine running clearance for each bushing / journal, subtract previous camshaft
                    journal diameter reading from camshaft bushing inside diameter reading. See
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_349.xml" xrefid="E30009A">Specifications
                        <xref refid="E30009A"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If maximum allowable running clearance is exceeded, measure cam journal outside diameter
                    and cam bushing inside diameter again and compare with
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_349.xml" xrefid="E30009A">Specifications
                        <xref refid="E30009A"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    . See camshaft bushing removal and installation procedures within this section.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate new camshaft bushings and crankcase bores with clean engine oil.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
